Docker Image Push Commands
Retrieve Authentication Token
Authenticate your Docker client to your registry using the AWS CLI.

docker login -u AWS https://058264459447.dkr.ecr.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com -p 
      
docker login -u AWS https://058264459447.dkr.ecr.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com -p 

    
If you receive an error using the AWS CLI, make sure that you have the latest version of the AWS CLI and Docker installed.

Build Docker Image
Build your Docker image using the provided command.

docker build -t <your_image_name> .
      
docker build -t <your_image_name> .

    
You can skip this step if your image is already built.

Tag Docker Image
Tag your image so you can push the image to this repository.

docker tag <your_image_name>:latest 058264459447.dkr.ecr.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/highwind/985c76c0-f2c2-4913-983f-2ea6a27e3f7f/eab9a693-f9b2-42d8-8980-8a181f05af85:latest

Push Docker Image
